readme: ## has-own-property-x Used to determine whether an object has an own property with the specified property key. ### `module.exports(object, property)` boolean The `hasOwnProperty` method returns a boolean indicating whether the `object` has the specified `property`. Does not attempt to fix known issues in older browsers, but does ES6ify the method. **Kind**: Exported function **Returns**: boolean - `true` if the property is set on `object`, else `false`. **Throws**: - TypeError If object is null or undefined. | Param | Type | Description | | -------- | ------------------------------------------ | ------------------------------------------- | | object | Object | The object to test. | | property | string \| Symbol | The name or Symbol of the property to test. | **Example** ```js import hasOwnProperty from 'has-own-property-x'; const o = { foo: 'bar', }; console.log(hasOwnProperty(o, 'bar')); // false console.log(hasOwnProperty(o, 'foo')); // true hasOwnProperty(undefined, 'foo'); // TypeError: Cannot convert undefined or null to object ```
